Present interval One and Default is performing two Updates per One draw.
This is extremely buggy consider if you cant get two updates done in one time slice.
In Xna you would skip a draw it would all work out. With this if you skip a draw your doing 4 updates to get one draw out. **I tested this with a empty project in just game1.**

In the top image you can see that when is FixedTimeStep is off, im getting 30fps or doing 60 updates and draws at a 1 to 1 ratio. Update Draw took 2 seconds to execute 60 times. in other words my TargetElapsedTime has been halfed. I should be getting like 120 or more as fast as my system can go.

