On line 1405 or so of the GraphicsDevice.DirectX WindowsUAP build you are missing a compile conditional that includes these lines:

```
            //You can't Map the BackBuffer surface, so we copy to another texture
            using (var dxgiBackBuffer = _swapChain.GetBackBuffer<Surface>(0))
            using (var backBufferTexture = dxgiBackBuffer.QueryInterface<SharpDX.Direct3D11.Texture2D>())
```

UAP does not define WINDOWS or WINDOWS_STOREAPP. I tried adding WINDOWS_UAP and it seemed to be ok.
# if WINDOWS || WINDOWS_STOREAPP || WINDOWS_UAP

```
            //You can't Map the BackBuffer surface, so we copy to another texture
            using (var dxgiBackBuffer = _swapChain.GetBackBuffer<Surface>(0))
            using (var backBufferTexture = dxgiBackBuffer.QueryInterface<SharpDX.Direct3D11.Texture2D>())
```
